==English==
=== Alternative spellings ===
* Yahbulon, Jabulon

=== Substantive Adjective ===
'''Jahbulon''' 
# A compound [[ritual]] word [[w:York Rite| York Rite Freemasons]] have historically used. As a substantive adjective - convention assigns to it the singular masculine gender. 

==== Etymology ====

* First, that it is a compound of [[יה|יָהּ]] ''(Yah,'' [[Yahweh]]) + [[בעל|בּעל]] ''(bul,'' on high, in heaven) + [[און|אוֹן]] ''(’on,'' [[strength]]).  This is the etymology currently advocated by Masons; to emphasise reverence for God and proclaim Him in no uncertain terms as "The True and Living God — The Most High — The Almighty".
Reference: ''The Rev’d Canon Richard Tydeman, An Address to Grand Chapter, (of England), 13th November 1985.''

* Second, that it may have been a [[blend]] of Hebrew [[יה|יָהּ]] ''(Yah,'' [[Yahweh]]) + [[זבולון|זְבוּלוּן]] ''(Zəbūlūn,'' [[Zebulun]] or [[Zabulon]], son of Jacob).

=== Porper Noun ===
'''Jahbulon''' 
# A compound [[ritual]] word historically missquoted as a proper noun by occultists and anti-masonic authors. ''No'' masonic use is made in this manner.

==== Etymology ====

* Third, it is explained as being a combination of Hebrew [[יה|יָהּ]] ''(Yah,'' [[Yahweh]]) + [[בעל|בּעל]] ''(bul,'' indicating [[Baal]]), + [[און|אוֹן]] ''(’On,'' [[On]], a city of Egypt, explained as a reference to [[Osiris]], perhaps as a misunderstanding of Genesis 46:20).  This commonly-given derivation is particularly [[deprecated]] by Masons. '''2004,''' Ralph Ellis, ''Eden in Egypt'' [http://books.google.com/books?ie=UTF-8&hl=en&id=ValvQKcqTGgC&pg=PA224&lpg=PA224&sig=PokIUjvdPlMMX5VoQV_p7wxJqwU]

